for  ...  each  loop  Vs  Regular  for  loop
---------------------------------------------
1) What  is  the  syntax  of  for  ...  each  loop ?  --->  for(datatype  variable :  array / collection / enum)
														statements
    What  is  the  syntax  of  regular  for  loop ?  --->  for(Initialization ;   condition ;  increment / decrement)
    	     													statements

2) What  does  for ... each  loop  do ?  --->  Iterates  thru  array  /  collection / enum
     What  does  regular  for  loop  do ?  --->  Iterates  thru  index  of  each  element  in  the  array  /  collection

3) How  is  each  element  of  array  denoted  in  for ...  each  loop ?  --->  'x' 
                                                                                                                    Eg:  for(int  x :  array)
														                    System . out . pintln(x)
    How  is  each  element  of  array  denoted  in  regular  for  loop ?  --->  a[i]  where  'a'  is  an  array
    
4) Which  loop  is  simple  in  syntax ?   --->  for  each  loop  becoz  there  is  no  initialization , condition  and  increment

5) Which  loop  is  powerful ?  --->  Regular  for  loop  becoz  it  can  track  both  indexes  and  elements

6) What  is  the  issue  with  for  ...  each  loop ?  --->  It  can  track  elements  only  but  not  their  indexes

7) int  x;
    for(x :  a)
    	   statements;
    Is  the  for  loop  valid  ?  ---->  No  becoz  'x'  is  not  declared  in  for  ...  each   loop

8) int  i;
    for(i = 0 ; i <= a . length - 1 ; i++)
    	   statements;
    Is  the  for  loop  valid  ?  ---->  Yes  becoz  'i'  can  be  declared  separately  but  not  necessarily  in  for  loop

9) When  is  for ... each  loop  recommended ?  --->  To  iterate  thru  array , collection  and  enum
